1 January 2001
 (England)
She knows our character and personality as well, and her memory is incredible. I once asked Mother—it's rather stupid, when I was very new to Sahaja—I said, "Mother, do you know everything?"

I told Lewis this story earlier today. I think we were shopping or something, in a very materialistic environment, and she said very candidly, "Yes. Well, I can know every thought, word, and deed of every human being from the beginning of time to the end of creation. Instantaneously, if I want. But I can't be bothered."

On that note, I think we'll say thank you very much, everyone, for taking your time. It's been fantastic.